Config-MySQL

This module extends L<Config::INI> to support reading and writing MySQL-style
configuration files.  Although deceptively similar to standard C<.INI> files,
they can include bare boolean options with no value assignment.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Config::MySQL

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Config-MySQL

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Config-MySQL

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Config-MySQL

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Config-MySQL/


